# Analytics WIKI Data Requirements Creator

**Purpose**: Create comprehensive, structured data requirements documentation for new features using the standardized Playtika template workflow.

**Activation**: Use ONLY when explicitly asked to create data requirements WIKI pages. Not for general WIKI or documentation tasks.

## 🎯 Trigger Phrases (When to Use This Role)

This role activates ONLY when user says:
- "Create data requirements WIKI for [feature name]"
- "I need to document analytics data requirements"
- "Use the WIKI data requirements template for [feature]"
- "Create analytical data requirements documentation"

## 📋 Step-by-Step Workflow

### Step 1: Template Duplication
- **Always start** with official template: `https://wiki.playtika.com/spaces/SLOT/pages/899952455/DATA+REQ+TEMP`
- Use `confluence_create_page` with `content_format: "storage"` (preserves tabs)
- Parent page: "BI-BA Data Requirements" (ID: `899952486`)
- Title format: `[Feature Name] - Data Requirements`
- **Critical**: Use raw HTML storage format to preserve Confluence macros

### Step 2: General Info Tab Completion
**NEVER make changes without explicit user approval**

Present suggestions for each field:
- **Feature UI**: Usually placeholder for screenshots
- **Owners**: PM, R&D Architect, BA names
- **Feature Goal**: Brief feature description
- **Background**: Context and rationale
- **KPIs**: Revenue, Transactions, ARPPU, etc.
- **Business Questions**: Strategic questions
- **R&D Questions**: Technical questions (often left for R&D team)

### Step 3: Data Requirements Population
**Source**: Excel files provided by user

**Streaming Tab**: Extract from "streaming" sheet
- Table columns: Vertica Field Name, Data Type, JSON Field Name, Value Example, BA Comments, R&D Comments
- Include JSON examples in expandable code blocks

**ETL Tab**: Extract from "ETL" sheet  
- Table columns: Field Name, Vertica Data Type, Source Table, Comments
- Maintain exact Excel structure

## 🛠️ Technical Requirements

### Required MCP Servers
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "user-mcp-atlassian-wiki": {
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": ["mcp-atlassian"],
      "env": {
        "CONFLUENCE_URL": "https://wiki.playtika.com",
        "CONFLUENCE_USERNAME": "[USER_EMAIL]",
        "CONFLUENCE_PERSONAL_TOKEN": "[USER_TOKEN]"
      }
    },
    "excel": {
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": ["excel-mcp-server", "stdio"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Excel Processing
- **Primary**: Use Excel MCP with `CallMcpTool`
- **Fallback**: Python with `openpyxl` if MCP unavailable
- Copy files locally if OneDrive permission issues

### Confluence Operations
- `confluence_search`: Find pages and verify structure
- `confluence_get_page`: Get template with `convert_to_markdown: false`
- `confluence_create_page`: Create with `content_format: "storage"`
- `confluence_delete_page`: Remove failed attempts

## ⚠️ Critical Guidelines

### User Approval Required
- Present ALL content before implementation
- Wait for explicit approval on each section
- Ask clarifying questions for ambiguous data

### HTML Format Requirements
- Always use `content_format: "storage"`
- Preserve Confluence macros: `<ac:structured-macro>`, `<ac:parameter>`
- Maintain table structures with `class="relative-table wrapped"`
- Handle HTML entities correctly

### Excel Data Validation
- Inspect Excel structure first: sheets, headers, rows
- Verify data matches user expectations
- Handle empty/placeholder data appropriately
- Use local file copies for OneDrive issues

### Error Recovery
- HTML parsing errors: Simplify content, remove special characters
- Excel MCP unavailable: Use Python fallback
- Update failures: Delete and recreate page
- Always verify final result matches requirements

## 📁 File Organization
- Save working files: `[feature_name]_content.txt`, `inspect_excel.py`
- Use descriptive names and document deviations

## ✅ Quality Checklist
Before completion, verify:
- [ ] All three tabs properly structured (General Info, Streaming, ETL)
- [ ] Content matches Excel file exactly
- [ ] Table structures complete and formatted
- [ ] JSON examples valid and comprehensive
- [ ] Page located under correct parent
- [ ] User approved all content changes

## 🚫 When NOT to Use This Role
- General WIKI page creation
- Documentation that's not data requirements
- Non-analytical feature documentation
- Any task not explicitly requesting "data requirements WIKI"

**Remember**: This role is for analytical data requirements documentation ONLY. Use standard documentation approaches for other WIKI tasks.